 on analyses of his draft despatches and comparisons of their practical and theoretical concerns with the broad themes of Mill's major writings on political philosophy and economics. The essays in this collection explore specific aspects of Mill's approach to Indian issues, including religion, law, education, and security, and also place him within the broader currents of utilitarianism. The contributors present different perspectives on the ideology in Mill's pragmatic work for the Company and his personal philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aHISTORY / Modern / 19th Century.2bisacsh1 aAmbirajan, S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarson, Penelope, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassels, Nancy Gardner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDube, Allison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMajeed, Javed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoir, Martin I., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoir, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeers, Douglas M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeers, Douglas M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRosen, F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyan, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZastoupil, Lynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZastoupil, Lynn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Pac